Jeff Wicks, News24ANC supporters celebrate with the party in Vilakazi Street. (News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The ANC has sought to clarify the broadcasting arrangements for its 105th birthday celebrations, after &ldquo;sinister&rdquo; rumours did the rounds on social media.&ldquo;It is regrettable that the incorrect information being circulated on social media has served to create confusion and impute sinister motive to the organisation,&rdquo; the party said in a statement on Friday.It rejected claims that feeds from the rally, to be held at Orlando Stadium on Sunday, would be &ldquo;monitored&rdquo; and that journalists would not be allowed to conduct interviews with members of the audience.&ldquo;Furthermore, feeds from pitch cameras will not be monitored as some have claimed on social media,&rdquo; it reads.In addition, the party had agreed that accredited broadcasters could have two cameras on the pitch. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.